summary: baby girl h asking daddy to paint her nails
question: baby girl h asking daddy to paint her nails
answer:
fuck meeeeeeeee

“y-you want daddy to paint your nails?”

harry stutters, looking at his almost three-year old baby angel who’s sitting beside him on the piano bench as she’s been doing ever since she could climb up chairs (but dad h doesn’t care, would still carry her up because he’s used to it and didn’t want to risk his angel getting hurt) and he feels at shock to be honest.

she nods her head up and down, her attention on his fingers as he’s been figuring up the keys and she wants whatever she has even if she knows what it’s called but could barely pronounce it without asking how it is pronounced first.

“o-okay then.”

he’d carry her up and rummage through the missus’ drawers first to get the nail lacquer he’s stuck in there, all while still holding his angel and she looks with curiosity.

harry uncaps it and looks at the awe-filled look on the missus’ face as she snaps pictures of it and even gotten out the polaroid, uncapping the bottle and he swipes the lacquer and he almost couldn’t focus because he isn’t the best at this and the amused laugh of his bub distracts her.

but as he finishes and bubby bites her lips smiling and waves her hands around looks up at him, he’s just about lost it and it’s his weakness — literally making his knees weak and his eyes water.

“love you more than y’know.”

summary: The Potter Twins and the Philosopher's Stone
title: The Potter Twins and the Philosopher's Stone
body:
On that fateful Halloween night when James and Lily Potter are murdered, their infant twins, Harry and Aralynn, are sent to live in separate homes—Aralynn with a magical family, and Harry with an ordinary one. However, when they’re both accepted to Hogwarts, and things start to get spooky.

Recognition

When the moon took the sun’s place in the sky, and all stragglers from the Common Room had gone; Aralynn Weasley, Ron Weasley, Hermione Granger, and Harry Potter prepared to walk directly into danger….

Read more…

blog.name: wellthatwasaletdown
blog.title: Former Harrie Club
blog.description:
I created this as a place for former Harry fans who have recently been turned off by his promotion and solo rollout and are now just confused and want to have open discourse about it. I accept submitted posts and will post anything that is not derogatory or rude. Please keep it civil, we are here to talk not belittle each other. Attackers will be blocked.NEW: I will now be cutting off or removing submissions that are just repeating discussions that have already taken place. Please read back if you have a question, chances are it's been answered. As an added note, we are aware that not all Harries are angry people but we sometimes generalize due to character limits, apologies in advance but we know there are many lovely, kind, friendly Harries out there and we don't mean to offend you. <!-- Start of StatCounter Code for Tumblr -->

summary: Earlier on here an anon mentioned something they thought might be shade from Liam toward Harry. That made me think of something...
body: Earlier on here an anon mentioned something they thought might be shade from Liam toward Harry. That made me think of something that isn’t shade, but I like to pretend it is because it makes me smile! So team Holo set up that ridiculous mob scene at Harry’s hotel in Mexico and let his fans insult and rip each other apart over it. They also allowed rumors to run wild that he was deathly ill and completely traumatized by the entire event. Meanwhile, Liam’s posting videos to his Instagram of he and his fans having a sing-a-long at his hotel in the same city, along with loads of fans posting their own pics with a smiling Liam as he greeted everyone he met throughout the day. And this evening he had a totally free mini concert at his hotel in Brazil. He just told everybody and anybody to show up and enjoy. So two fan related events for Liam that were fun and happy. One of which was in the same city as all those “terrible" fans that poor Harry had to suffer through. It makes me laugh to think that one minute Harry the victim is terrorized by a mob, and the next minute Liam’s there in the same city having the nicest time. There was also discussion on here yesterday about whether or not Harry’s uber expensive Lane One tickets sold, and then today Liam does a surprise show that’s completely free. Again, I know it’s not actually shade, but it’s fun to pretend because Liam comes out smelling like a rose. While Harry’s still trying to be Mr. Mystery I’m-Too-Famous, Liam’s out there just being himself and being nice to everyone. And in turn, everyone around him is having a great time. He’s happy and his fans are happy. Funny that when you actually treat people with kindness, instead of just selling t-shirts with the words printed on them, people are kind to you as well.
